{"lemma":"نَقِيبِ","slug":"نَقِيبِ","root":"ن.ق.ب","root_slug":"ن-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَقِيب","root":"نقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40334"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"captain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leader, chief"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"magistrate, head of a community"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prefect, governor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intelligent man"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"master of ceremonies"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tongue of a balance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pipe, flute"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/na.qiːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40334","headword_ar":"نَقِيبٌ","root":"nqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoquwbN","text_ar":"مَنْقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perforated, pierced, bored."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a hole made through,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiybN","text_ar":"نَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A musical reed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pipe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tongue of a pair of scales,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"balance"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  A dog"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the upper part of his mindpipe"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galoSamatuhu","text_ar":"غَلْصَمَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the S, K or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his windpipe,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hanojaratuhu","text_ar":"حَنْجَرَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perforated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that his cry may be weak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a base man performs this operation on his dog, in order that guests may not hear its cry. (S: and the like is said in the L.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiybu quwomK","text_ar":"نَقِيبُ قُوْمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The intendant, superintendent, overseer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inspector, of a people; he who takes notice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cognisance, of their actions, and is responsible for them; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eariyfuhumo","text_ar":"عَرِيفُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhiduhumo","text_ar":"شَاهِدُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Damiyuhumo","text_ar":"ضَمِيُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiynN","text_ar":"اَمِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafiylN","text_ar":"كَفِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariyfN","text_ar":"عَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is set over a people, and investigates their affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the greatest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supreme, chief of a people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called [from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaba","text_ar":"نَقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he scrutinized, or investigated, ”] because he is acquainted with the secret"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2835},{"kind":"text","text":"affairs of the people, and knows their virtues, or generous actions, and is the way by which one obtains knowledge of their affairs: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqabaA'u","text_ar":"نُقَبَاءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Zj","TA","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}